                                <condition key="deficient">
                                  The manuscript is in bad condition. The upper board is broken in two halves and the outer is missing, together with the lower board.
                                  A large loss is present in the central area of <locus target="#1"/>. Most folia are stained and darkened along the margins but the most severe damage is caused by insects.
                                  Apart from the presence of insect droppings, insects have eaten the upper part of the quires also damaging the sewing. Therefore, the leaves became loose.
                                  The damage also extends to the satchel.
                                </condition>
