                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="Ethiopian">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                  The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                  The upper board broke and only the inner half of the upper board is preserved. The preserved fragment of the upper board is flush with the bookblock and has shallow external bevels.
                                  The grain runs vertically. The external surface and the edges of the board fragment are polished and a finishing layer of dark colour has been added.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="SewingStations">2</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4">
                                  Chainstitch sewing on two sewing stations (one pair); Z-plied thread.
                                  The sewing broke because of the insect damage and the <ref target="#q6">sixth quire<ref/> has been connected with the rest of
                                  the bookblock by stitching it with simple loops of thread to the chain on the spine.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Spine">
                                  The small pairs of holes close to the tail of the quires might be what remains of endbands or quire tackets.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SlipCase">
                                  The manuscript is provided with a leather one-piece single-walled slip case with a cord hinging strap.
                                  The case is equipped with two flaps extending from the side panels and a main pointed flap extending from the back to the front
                                  panel to cover the opening of the book compartment.
                                  The cord hanging strap passes through two flaps extending from the bottom panel of the case.
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
